title: $:/plugins/rimir/cascade-palette/changelog
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.0.129 |2026-06-11 |''Fix: inline editors in the side-preview pane now work — including framed (iframe) editors like sq/streams' notes.'' Two bugs surfaced by rendering an editable Streams note-structure in the pane (see rimir/kind's new ''Notes'' preview). ''(1) Render into an attached node'' (`cp-side-preview.js` `_renderSidePreview`) — the preview widget tree was rendered into a ''detached'' `<div>` and appended to the pane afterwards. On a rebuild while an inline editor was open (e.g. returning to a note still in edit mode), the editor's engine read `ownerDocument.defaultView` during `render()` on the not-yet-attached node → `null` → the whole preview render threw (''Cannot read properties of null (reading 'document')'') and was cached as that error until reload. Now the container is appended ''before'' `render()`, giving such engines a live window. ''(2) Keystrokes (incl. Space) stayed with the editor, not the palette input'' (`cp-side-preview.js` `_keydownTargetIsInsidePreviewWidget`). A framed editor (sq/streams, the core body editor) keeps its editable in an `<iframe>` and ''re-dispatches'' each keydown onto a parent wrapper (`SPAN.tc-keyboard`) so TW shortcuts work across the iframe boundary; that wrapper isn't an editable tag, so the interactivity guard (which only looked at `e.target`) returned false, `handleKeydown` ran, and the type-ahead redirect stole every character to the palette input. The guard now ALSO consults `document.activeElement`: when focus is on an `<iframe>` / textarea / input / contenteditable inside the pane, the keystroke belongs to that editor and the cascade leaves it alone. Candidate pills are excluded from both detection paths, so ←/→ pill-cycling is unaffected. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-side-preview.js`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS module — server restart required. |
|0.0.128 |2026-06-11 |''Fix: ←/→ now switch candidate templates in the side-preview pane.'' The pane's keyboard handler (`cp-side-preview.js` `_handleKeydownPreview` — Esc → input, ←/→ cycle candidate pills via `_cyclePreviewActive`) was fully implemented but never reachable: the keyboard dispatch table in `cp-keyboard.js` ''deliberately omitted'' the `preview` row (a stale NOTE claimed candidate switching was click-only), so a keystroke on the focused pane resolved to no handler and the arrows did nothing. Added the `"preview": "_handleKeydownPreview"` dispatch row (the handler lives in the sibling `cp-side-preview` module — both are applied to the same prototype at boot) and rewrote the NOTE. The drift-detector spec now applies ''both'' modules to its stub, and the dispatch-table specs assert `preview` resolves to `_handleKeydownPreview`. Click-cycling and the single-candidate suppression are unchanged. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-keyboard.js`, `test/test-keyboard-dispatch.js`, `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules — server restart required. |
|0.0.127 |2026-06-11 |''Date rows: offset prefill + optional calendar popup + in-edit `+/-` nudge.'' Three additions to the `ca-kind: date` control, driven by `rimir/kind`'s tickler create-wizard. ''(1) `ca-date-default`'' (`cp-items.js` `dateDefault`; `cp-firing.js` `enterEditMode`) — a smart-date / offset expr (`+2w`, `today`, `2026-07-01`) that seeds a ''still-blank'' date field the first time its editor opens, so a wizard date step lands pre-filled. Fires lazily on edit-entry (not just stage-push like daterange's `ca-default-start/-end`), so it works for a date row that appears mid-stage. The smart-date→storage conversion is factored into shared `_smartDateToStorage` (reused by `_seedRangeField`). ''(2) Calendar popup'' (`cp-firing.js` `_attachDatePicker` / teardown in `exitEditMode`; new config `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/date-picker-module`) — when that config names a `module-type: library` tiddler exporting a Pikaday-compatible constructor, the palette attaches it to the edit input so the field gains a click-to-pick calendar. Display + storage go through the scribe date-helpers (no moment-format coupling). ''Decoupled'': empty / missing config = keyboard-only (unchanged); the public plugin carries no hard dependency on a date-picker (my-wiki points it at kixam's pikaday). ''(3) In-edit `+/-` nudge'' (`cp-keyboard.js` `_handleKeydownEdit`; `cp-firing.js` `_syncDateEditInput`) — `+/-` (Shift ±month, Ctrl ±year) now nudges the date ''while in typed-edit mode'' too (previously only on the selected row), keeping the input + calendar in sync; needed because single-field wizard date steps auto-open into edit mode. The calendar is appended to `<body>` (`bound` mode) since the popup + cascade column are `overflow:hidden`, force-`show()`n on attach (the input is already focused), and floated above the backdrop via `.pika-single.rcp-datepicker` (`styles.tid`). ''(4) Auto-open race fix'' (`cp-rendering.js` `_maybeAutoOpen`) — the auto-fire token is now marked consumed ''inside'' the deferred action (past the editMode/stack guards) instead of synchronously, so a step that auto-opens an editor AND carries an (already-valid) auto-advance row no longer orphans the advance token: it fires correctly once the edit commits. Fixes a wizard step with an optional `ca-step-auto-edit` field (e.g. tickler `until`) not advancing after an empty ↵. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-items.js`, `widgets/cp-firing.js`, `widgets/cp-keyboard.js`, `widgets/cp-rendering.js`, `widgets/cp-constants.js`, `styles.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules — server restart required. |
|0.0.126 |2026-06-10 |''Guided-flow primitives: above-input heading bar, auto-open rows, tree-node Enter/Right split, and `pop-to-actions`.'' Five new declarative props that let a plugin build a hands-free, multi-step drill flow (first consumer: `rimir/kind`'s create-wizard). ''(1) Heading bar'' — a new non-selectable `.rcp-heading` banner above the input (`cascade-palette-widget.js` `headingEl`; `cp-rendering.js` `renderHeading`; `styles.tid`). A pushed stage sets it via `ca-next-heading`; a stage whose content swaps in place refreshes it per recompute from a row's `ca-stage-heading` (`cp-stack.js` `_applyDynamicStageMeta`). `ca-next-force-headers` still forces group headers on a single-cluster stage. ''(2) Auto-open'' — `ca-auto` (`edit`\|`drill`\|`fire`) + `ca-auto-token`: the first armed auto-row in a freshly-rendered stage is acted on once per token (`cp-rendering.js` `_maybeAutoOpen`, tracked in `stage._autoFiredTokens`), so a flow lands directly in the relevant input/picker. ''(3) Tree-node semantics'' — `ca-enter-fires: yes` opts a synthetic `ca-items-from` drill row into Enter-fires-`ca-actions` / Right-drills-children (the By-Namespace tree-node gesture), incl. exemption from `drillSelected`'s pre-fire (`cp-firing.js`, `cp-items.js`). ''(4) `ca-after-fire: pop-to-actions`'' — fire then pop every stage down to the nearest action-menu stage (or root), keeping the palette open, so a multi-step create flow returns the user to the originating entity instead of closing (`cp-firing.js`). ''Touches:'' `widgets/cascade-palette-widget.js`, `widgets/cp-rendering.js`, `widgets/cp-stack.js`, `widgets/cp-firing.js`, `widgets/cp-items.js`, `styles.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `doc/protocol.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules — server restart required. |
|0.0.125 |2026-06-09 |''Match highlight is now always visible, and the default search matches the displayed label.'' Two long-standing disconnects fixed so the user can always see WHY a row matched. ''(1) The matcher now targets the displayed label.'' `cp-actions.js#_resolveMetaField` resolves the `name` search key to ''`_displayNameForItem(item)`'' — the active name-lens / row-label projection (e.g. the `caption`), exactly what's shown — instead of the raw `item.name` (which for data rows is the tiddler title). So in a caption-lensed view (e.g. //All tiddlers//) typing matches the caption you see, and the match coordinates index into that string. The deep-search twin (`cp-deep-search.js#_matchItemAll`) shares `_resolveMetaField`, so it inherits the fix. ''(2) The renderer highlights the label in place.'' `cp-rendering.js#_renderRowNameContent` no longer skips the highlight when a name-lens override fired — it highlights the displayed label (coords now align). Label and hint matches are found by scanning `_matches` (not just the first `_match`), so both can highlight at once. ''(3) Every match is guaranteed visible.'' Matches drawn inline (label / hint) are tracked per-row (`_inlineDrawn`); the snippet pass renders a highlighted snippet line below the row for ''every'' other match — a Search-field hit (text / title / …), or a label match under a rich-markup template lens that can't carry an inline highlight. Nothing matches invisibly. ''(4) Default search scope = the displayed label only'' (`_defaultSearchFields` + `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/search-fields-default`: `name hint` → `name`). `hint` is now opt-in (push the Hint Meta pill). ''(5) New shipped 🆔 Title Search-field pill'' (`search-field/title.tid`) so a row stays findable by its raw title even when the label is a caption (surfaces as a snippet). ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-actions.js`, `widgets/cp-rendering.js`, `search-field/title.tid` (new), `search-meta/name.tid`, `settings.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `doc/protocol.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid` (deep-search verified, unchanged). JS modules — server restart required. |
|0.0.124 |2026-06-09 |''New `rimir-cascade-palette-drill-sequence` message — programmatic create-then-land-in-context'' (`cp-constants.js` `DRILL_SEQUENCE_MESSAGE`; `cascade-palette-widget.js` `openDrillSequence`). Action wikitext can now push, onto the ''live'' stack (opening fresh only if the palette is closed), an intermediate `items-from` list stage and — on top of it — an action-menu stage for a specific entity, leaving the palette open on that menu. Popping returns to the list, then to the pre-existing drill chain (the "how I got here" stack is preserved). The `host` param becomes the list stage's `parentPicked`, so its `items-from` filter can reference `<<parent-picked>>`; `select` pre-highlights a row in the list. Params: `items-from`, `host`, `title`, `entity-type`, `entity`, `entity-title`, `select` (≥1 of `items-from` / `entity` required). Built for `rimir/worga`'s reworked ''Take call'' (create a conversation, then land on it with the person's conversation list as the pop-target). Docs: message table in `doc/reference.tid`. ''Touches:'' `widgets/cp-constants.js`, `widgets/cascade-palette-widget.js`, `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules — server restart required. |
|0.0.123 |2026-06-08 |''Two extensibility features: action providers + a `daterange` edit kind.'' ''(1) Action providers (`cp-constants.js` `ACTION_PROVIDER_TAG`; `cp-stack.js#loadProviderActions`).'' A fifth action-discovery path, unioned into `loadActionsForType`: a tiddler tagged ''`$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/action-provider`'' with `ca-applies` (gate filter, `<currentTiddler>` = focused row) + `ca-provider-items` (filter returning ''one JSON-encoded action spec per result'' — same shape as a drill's `ca-items-from` rows) emits N actions ''computed from the focused row''. Lets a consumer surface row-derived actions (e.g. rimir/kind's one "Manage <ref-field>…" per reference field) without hand-authoring a tiddler each. Parse-guarded with `console.warn`. ''(2) New `daterange` edit kind'' (`cp-items`/`cp-rendering`/`cp-firing`/`cp-keyboard`/`cp-stack`). One row binding ''two'' date fields — `ca-bind-field` (start) + `ca-bind-field-end` (end) — rendered side-by-side (`01.07.2026 → 15.07.2026`) with the active side boxed. ''←/→'' switch the active sub-date, ''+/-'' adjust it (bare = day, Shift = month, Ctrl = year), ''Space/Enter'' type it via the smart parser; ''↑/↓'' stay as normal menu navigation (arrow down to Save — no escape gesture). A ''fresh'' range (both fields empty) is seeded once on stage entry from `ca-default-start` / `ca-default-end` (smart-date exprs like `+2w`, `today`, `2026-07-01`) — a range that already has values is left untouched, so one row serves both create-with-defaults and edit-existing. `ca-on-commit` fires after every adjustment (so a derived caption/title tracks live). Reuses the date kind's arithmetic + storage via a per-side throwaway sub-item (`_rangeSubItem`); the modifier→unit mapping is unified in `_dateUnitForEvent` (single source of truth for date + daterange, on both +/- and ↑/↓). Deep-search auto-skips the kind. Docs: protocol (worked example 8b) + reference (keystrokes, fields, `ca-kind` row) updated. |''Sort menu lists by the displayed (lensed) name; selected-on-top pickers.'' Two related changes so on-screen order matches what the user reads. ''(1) View sorts (`cp-views.js#_sortRowsForView`).'' The `alphabetical` / `natural` (and default) name sorts now key on each row's ''displayed'' name — the active name-lens / row-label projection (e.g. the `caption` from the shipped ''Caption → Title'' lens) via the new `_displayNameForItem` helper — instead of the raw `item.name` (often a `$:/…` or path title). Previously a caption-lensed view sorted by title while showing captions, so the list looked unsorted (e.g. ''All tiddlers'', ''By namespace''). `by-field` / `custom` sorts are unchanged (they use the author's field / key). ''(2) Data-row pickers (`cp-stack.js#_sortDataRowItems`).'' `ca-next-scope` (tiddler-title) filter stages now sort unconditionally — selected rows first, then alphanumeric by displayed name. Synthetic `ca-items-from` stages opt in via a new ''`ca-sort-rows: name`'' field on the parent drill (structured menus omit it to keep their authored `ca-order` layout). A row counts as selected when it's a `toggle` whose bound field holds its `ca-true-value` (read via `isToggleOn`) OR carries the new ''`ca-selected: yes`'' flag (for non-toggle single-select leaves). Order is frozen per stage VISIT (`stage._dataRowOrder`) so Space-toggling a row on/off doesn't make it jump out from under the keyboard cursor; re-entry re-applies selected-on-top. `_displayNameForItem` lives in `cp-items.js` (shared by view + data-row sorts; guarded so item-only test widgets fall back to `item.name`). ''(3)'' Demo: the ''Hybrid'' view's `ca-view-containers-first` flipped to `no` so its drills read as one continuous alphanumeric run rather than containers-then-leaves. Docs: `ca-sort-rows` / `ca-selected` + the lensed-name sort note added to protocol + reference. Tests: +3 Jasmine specs (`test-sort-display-name.js`). |
|0.0.121 |2026-06-08 |''Paginated result window ("Show more" / "Load all").'' The per-stage result list was a hard `slice(0, max-results)` (default 30) that silently dropped everything past the cap. Now, when more rows match than the visible window shows, the list ends with two synthetic sentinel rows — ''Show N more'' (`_windowGrow:"page"`, grows the window by one page) and ''Show all N'' (`_windowGrow:"all"`, reveals every match). Both are plain keyboard-selectable rows; Enter/click grows `stage.windowSize` and re-slices in place (`cp-stack.js#_applyResultWindow` + `_windowSentinelRow`; activation in `cp-firing.js#fireSelected`). After ''Show more'' the selection lands on the first newly-revealed row (repeat-Enter pages down); the window resets to one page whenever the query text changes. Applies to every stage kind incl. deep-search. New `$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/max-results-step` sets the page increment (defaults to the `max-results` page size). Render: muted dashed-separator sentinel rows skip all data-row decoration (`cp-rendering.js`, new `.rcp-row-show-more` / `.rcp-row-load-all`). Tests: +11 Jasmine specs (`test-result-window.js`). |
|0.0.120 |2026-06-08 |''Fix: command entries showed raw titles in the "Entries" view.'' The default ''Caption → Title'' name lens was relabeling palette commands (e.g. ''Find entity'') to their `$:/…` tiddler title in the ''Entries'' view, because that view surfaces entries through its own `ca-view-roots: [...tag[entry]]` filter rather than the built-in entries channel — so the rows were tagged `dataRow:true` and the lens applied. The data-row gate (`cp-views.js#_evaluateLayer`) now also exempts any row whose backing tiddler is tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/entry`, matching the built-in entries channel's existing exemption: commands keep their authored `ca-name` and skip name/icon lens decoration in every view. Tests: +2 Jasmine specs in `test-layer-source.js`. |
|0.0.119 |2026-06-08 |''Channel/view "Overview" rows.'' A channel (`ca-channel-preview`) or view (`ca-view-preview`) can name a summary template; the root stage then emits a synthetic ''Overview'' row — a non-drill no-op leaf, search-skipped, pinned to the top of its group (`_buildOverviewRows` + a `_pinTop` pass in `_sortRowsForView`). Focusing the row renders the template in the side preview; ''Enter'' moves focus into the preview pane. To make this work, the side preview now surfaces a ''selected'' row's own `ca-preview-template` (`_selectedRowPreview`), not only a drilled one, and the auto-open fallback anchors on the template even when the row has no title (`_activePreviewContext`). Optional `-preview-name` / `-preview-title` set the row/pill label and the caption above the body. New fields appear both in the long-tail field editors (`cp-view-edit-rows` / `cp-channel-edit-rows`, ''preview'' group) AND as an always-visible ''summary'' pill on the Structure strip's view header + each explicit channel mini-row (↵ edits, DEL clears, ''—'' when unset) via a new `summary` case in `_pillEditDescriptor`. Tests: +new Jasmine specs (`test-overview-rows.js`, `test-side-preview-rows.js`) + summary-pill descriptor specs in `test-view-editor.js`. |
|0.0.118 |2026-06-05 |''VIEW → CHANNEL restructuring + lens inheritance + richer presets.'' The structure-layer vocabulary is renamed to ''CHANNEL'' throughout: a CHANNEL is a named, reusable group of palette rows a view composes by reference (`ca-view-channels`). The data model moves `ca-layer-*` → `ca-channel-*`, the tag to `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/channel`, and the shipped channels to the `channels/` namespace; the parser ''dual-reads'' the old fields so un-migrated user tiddlers keep working, and a one-time browser startup migration (`cp-channel-migration`) rewrites them in place (idempotent, user-only, write-on-change). ''Lens inheritance:'' a view declares a default decoration lens per slot (`ca-view-lens-name`/`-icon`/`-annotation`); each channel may override (`ca-channel-lens-*`) or inherit, and the view can LOCK a slot (`ca-view-locked`) to force its lens everywhere. Resolution is now channel-aware — the same tiddler can decorate differently in two channels — baked once per view-load (`_applyLensInheritance`) and keyed into the row-decoration cache by channel. The three standalone lens-chooser strips are ''relocated'' into the Structure strip's view→channel tree (a view-default chooser per slot in the view row + a per-channel override chooser in each channel row, with inherit/lock cues; `l` toggles a lock; new-lens creation moves to Manage lenses) — the old strip rendering, focus/Tab-cycle plumbing and strip-driven lens-edit flow (`_renderLensStrip` / `_handleKeydownLensSlot` / `_beginLensEdit` / `_commitLensEdit` etc.) are fully removed, and the shared dual-read helpers live in `cp-utils`. ''Presets'' now capture/restore all six transient subsystems — filters, visibility, reach, search-meta, search-field, and sticky-context (schema `v:2`); a v1 preset restores the new subsystems to empty (lenses are deliberately excluded — they travel with the view). Tests: +19 Jasmine specs (`test-lens-inheritance`, `test-lens-choosers`, `test-presets`) plus updated rename specs. |
|0.0.117 |2026-06-04 |''Large root-set perf warning (Phase 6).'' A view whose root set resolves to more rows than a configurable threshold (`$:/config/rimir/cascade-palette/large-root-set-warning`, default 2000; `0` disables) now emits a one-time `console.warn` — that full set is rebuilt and re-decorated on every keystroke, so it's the dominant per-keystroke cost. The warning fires once per view + stage-kind (not per keystroke) and re-arms when the set drops back below the threshold, suggesting a narrower `ca-view-roots` or a filter pill (`cp-stack`: `getLargeRootSetWarning` / `_maybeWarnLargeRootSet`, called from `recomputeStage`). Adjustable live via Settings → Large root-set warning. Tests: +10 Jasmine specs (`test-large-root-set.js`) and +2 Playwright specs (`cascade-palette-perf.spec.js`). |
|0.0.116 |2026-06-04 |''In-palette entry + action editors (Phase 5).'' Two new top-level entries — ''📋 Manage entries'' and ''⚡ Manage actions'' — make command entries and actions authorable without hand-editing tiddlers, completing the in-palette definition-editor arc (views / layers / axes / lenses / entries / actions). Each lists every definition with a ''+ New …'' creator (prompt a name → save a fresh tagged tiddler with sane defaults → reopen) and one drillable row per definition. Drilling opens a per-facet field editor (`cp-entry-edit-rows`: identity / kind / leaf-behaviour / drill-target; `cp-action-edit-rows`: identity / the three discovery facets entity-type·applies·action-when / behaviour), binding each field in place via `ca-bind-*`, with a confirm-gated delete. USER definitions edit in place; a SHIPPED (shadow-only) one is clone-protected (''Clone to a custom … to edit''). One generic lifecycle (`cp-def-editor`: new / clone / delete, spec-driven) and one generic list builder (`cp-def-rows`) serve both kinds; a shared `cp-row-builders` util supplies the text/toggle row shapes. Tests: +13 Jasmine specs (`test-def-editor.js`) and +3 Playwright specs (`cascade-palette-entries.spec.js`). |
|0.0.115 |2026-06-04 |''Long-tail view + layer field editors (Phase 4).'' The Structure strip edits a view's core structure (roots/children/leaf/label/axes) and enum facets (sort/include-entries/grouping) live; everything else is now editable from ''Manage views → Edit all fields…'' — a drill (`cp-view-edit-rows`) listing the exhaustive view-scoped long tail as `ca-bind-*` rows, grouped: ''identity'' (name/hint/icon/order), ''display'' (count-format + show-count / containers-first / show-action-preview / show-side-preview / context-aware yes-no toggles), ''sort detail'' (sort-field/sort-key), ''picking'' (pick-mode / pick-emits-filter / after-fire), and ''row defaults'' (row-hint/icon/order/next-scope/items-from — the per-row overrides not surfaced as pills). Each explicit structure-layer the view composes drills into its own editor (`cp-layer-edit-rows`: name, `ca-layer-source`, `ca-layer-include-position`, and the `ca-layer-row-*` defaults). USER views/layers edit in place; a SHIPPED (shadow-only) view offers fork-to-edit and a shipped layer a Structure-strip hint (editing in place would write an override). The drill targets the active view via a new `$:/state/…/active-view` mirror written by `_setActiveView`, self-healing to the default view. `ca-position-<view>` stays on the entry, not the view. Tests: +14 Jasmine specs (`test-view-edit-rows.js`) and +3 Playwright specs (`cascade-palette-view-fields.spec.js`, incl. a live toggle write + layer drill). |
|0.0.114 |2026-06-04 |''Fork view is now a deep clone (Phase 2 tail).'' ''Manage views → Fork current view'' (`_forkView`) previously copied only the view's `ca-view-*` fields and kept its layers/axes ''shared'' with the source — editing the fork's structure mutated the original. It now makes a fully independent persisted copy: every explicit structure-layer and grouping axis the view references is copied into a private title, with `ca-view-layers` / `ca-view-axes` / each forked layer's `ca-layer-axes` rewritten to the copies (new `_forkLayer` / `_forkAxis` / `_forkAxisChain`). Per-axis params are preserved (the chain re-serialises as JSON only when some entry carries params, else a plain title list); the built-in entries layer and any unresolvable reference pass through verbatim. Axis field-copy is shared with the axis editor (`cp-axis-editor`'s `_copyAxisFields`) and layer field-copy is factored into `_copyLayerFields` (also used by `_beginLayerEdit`) — no duplication. Tests: +10 Jasmine specs (`test-view-fork.js`: deep-copy, param preservation, entries/unresolvable passthrough, byte-level isolation, collision-safe titles) and +2 Playwright specs (`cascade-palette-fork.spec.js`: the real Manage-views → Fork loop on shipped ''Hybrid'' for layers and a seeded axis-bearing view for axes). |
|0.0.113 |2026-06-04 |''In-palette axis create / edit / delete (Phase 3).'' A new ''🧭 Manage axes'' entry (`entries/manage-axes.tid`) makes the axis mechanics editable, transparently via raw filters — mirroring ''Manage lenses''. (1) ''+ New axis…'' (`cp-axis-editor.js`) seeds a scratch axis and opens the raw `ca-axis-key` editor with a live ''✓ N matches'' count, then prompts a name and saves under `…/axes/`. (2) Each existing axis drills into a per-facet field editor (`cp-axis-edit-rows.js`): bind-edit name / hint / icon / order / key / label / sort / sort-keys / empty-label in place, with a read-only info row naming any `<axis-param-X>` placeholders (their values are set per use in a layer's chain), and a confirm-gated delete. (3) A shipped (shadow-only) axis is clone-protected — ''📋 Clone to a custom axis to edit'' (`_cloneAxisToUser`) copies it to `…/axes/` first. Created axes feed the existing Structure-strip chain picker. Tests: +14 Jasmine specs (`test-axis-edit-rows.js`, `test-axis-editor.js`) and a 5-spec Playwright suite (`cascade-palette-axes.spec.js`, incl. an end-to-end check that an axis chain buckets the tree). |
|0.0.112 |2026-06-04 |''Per-lens field editor + auto-resolve; test hardening.'' (1) ''Field editor'' — drilling a lens in ''Manage lenses'' now opens a per-facet editor (`widgets/cp-lens-edit-rows.js` / `cp-lens-rows.js` / `cp-lens-actions-rows.js`): bind-edit ''name / chip / when / order'' in place, toggle default slots, edit each slot's ''filter'' + ''template'', pick the actions mode, and confirm-delete — all via the standard declarative `ca-bind-*` rows (replaces the prior `EDIT_LENS_MESSAGE` single-filter edit). Shipped lenses are clone-protected (''📋 Clone to a custom lens to edit'' → `CLONE_LENS_MESSAGE`). (2) ''Auto-resolve (no silent override)'' — a slot renders its filter OR its template and the filter wins; each row now carries a `ca-on-commit` that clears its sibling on a non-blank commit (last-edited wins; blank-commit promotes the other), plus a conflict marker (''filter ● active'' / ''template ⚠ ignored'') for pre-existing both-set lenses. (3) ''Fix'' — removed the dead `"preview"` row from the keyboard dispatch table: the `_handleKeydownPreview` it pointed at was never actually defined (the 0.0.108 "wired up" was incomplete), so it was a no-op; preview stays a focus in the Tab cycle with native scroll + click-to-switch candidate pills. (4) ''Tests'' — +11 lens-adjacent Jasmine specs (4-path action union, default-slot re-seed, `_cloneLensToUser`, row-icon applies/payload) and a new Playwright E2E suite (lenses / lens-editor / nav / structure / extras) covering the browser-only rendering (annotation chip + rich template) unit tests can't reach. |
|0.0.111 |2026-06-04 |''Lenses — actions, templates + annotation, and a Manage-lenses list.'' (1) ''Actions via lens'' — `ca-lens-actions` lets a lens contribute actions: `via-entity-type` declares it owns the standard entity-type bridge (the kind lens), any other value is a filter returning action titles to surface on a row. Always-on — gated only by `ca-lens-when`, never by slot selection, so kind actions stay available with the Icon slot off. Unions into `loadActionsForType` as a fourth path. (2) ''Template projections + annotation slot'' — `ca-lens-<slot>-template` renders rich wikitext per visible row (output HTML cached per data-change; filter wins when both set); the ''annotation'' slot now renders as a trailing chip. Ships generic ''Modified'' (filter) + ''Tags'' (template) annotation lenses (off by default). (3) ''Manage lenses list'' — the entry now lists every lens (''↵'' edit · ''DEL'' delete a custom lens) alongside a ''+ New … lens…'' creator per slot (`widgets/cp-lens-rows.js`); ''↵'' on a row edits via the new `EDIT_LENS_MESSAGE`. |
|0.0.110 |2026-06-04 |''Lenses — unified row-decoration model.'' The former row-label (name) + structure-toggle (icon) subsystems are replaced by one ''lens'' (tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/lens`) projecting ''name'' / ''icon'' / ''annotation'' slots via `ca-lens-<slot>-filter`, gated by `ca-lens-when`, seeded by `ca-lens-default`. Each slot is its own single-select chooser strip below the view strip. ''In-palette authoring'' (new `cp-lens-editor.js`): the ''➕ New…'' slot pill / ''Manage lenses'' entry create a lens with a live-preview filter editor; ''e'' edits, ''DEL'' deletes (confirm). ''DEL on a view pill'' now deletes the view too (confirm; shipped views refuse). One merged per-row resolver + cross-render cache (`cp-row-decorations.js`, keyed by selection + change-count) so decorations persist across keystrokes. ''Fix:'' lenses no longer relabel palette command rows (entries-layer rows like "Find entity"). Removed `cp-row-label-pills.js` / `cp-structure-toggles.js`; a prior `…/row-label` pick resets once to the default name lens. |
|0.0.109 |2026-06-03 |''New extension point — structure toggles (tag `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/structure-toggle`): boolean on/off pills in the Structure strip's view header, flipped with Space/Enter. A toggle may carry `ca-struct-row-icon-filter` to supply a per-data-row leading icon while on (new `widgets/cp-structure-toggles.js`). Enables e.g. kind's "Kind icons" toggle.'' |
|0.0.108 |2026-06-03 |''Side-preview pane: ←/→ now cycle between candidate previews when two or more apply, applying each on landing (no Enter/Space). The handler and hint text already existed but `"preview"` was never registered in the keyboard dispatch table — now wired up; Esc-from-preview (return to input) also starts working as a side effect.'' |
|0.0.107 |2026-06-03 |''Single-select pill strips (view / preset / row-label) now apply on ←/→ landing — navigating onto a pill selects it, no Space/Enter needed. Space/Enter still work; preset's trailing "+" save pill stays an explicit gesture. Driven by a central `selectOnMove` descriptor flag in `_handleKeydownPillStrip`.'' |
|0.0.106 |2026-06-03 |''Shift-Tab now restores the focus you last held in the group you switch into (the menu row, the filter pill you were editing, …) instead of always snapping to input / the bottom-most pill; falls back to the old defaults when that slot has disappeared or was never visited.'' |
